				<div id=3D"bodyContent" class=3D"vector-body ve-init-mw-desktopArticleT=
arget-targetContainer" aria-labelledby=3D"firstHeading" data-mw-ve-target-c=
ontainer=3D"">
					<div class=3D"vector-body-before-content">
							<div class=3D"mw-indicators">
		</div>

						<div id=3D"siteSub" class=3D"noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encycl=
opedia</div>
					</div>
					<div id=3D"contentSub"><div id=3D"mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
				=09
				=09
					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"shortd=
escription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Cha=
nces of card combinations in poker</div>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poker" title=3D"Poker">poker=
</a>, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probability" title=3D"Pr=
obability">probability</a> of each type of 5-card <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Poker_hand" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Poker hand">hand=
</a> can be computed by calculating the proportion of hands of that type am=
ong all possible hands.
</p>
<meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc">
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"History">History</h2><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DPoker_probability&amp;=
action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"Edit section: History"><span>edit</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Probability and gambling have been ideas since long before the invention=
 of poker. The development of probability theory in the late 1400s was attr=
ibuted to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gambling" title=3D"Gambl=
ing">gambling</a>; when playing a game with high stakes, players wanted to =
know what the chance of winning would be. In 1494, Fra <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luca_Pacioli" title=3D"Luca Pacioli">Luca Pacioli</a> =
released his work <span title=3D"Latin-language text"><i lang=3D"la">Summa =
de arithmetica, geometria, proportioni e proportionalita</i></span> which w=
as the first written text on probability. Motivated by Pacioli's work, <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Girolamo_Cardano" class=3D"mw-redirect=
" title=3D"Girolamo Cardano">Girolamo Cardano</a> (1501=E2=80=931576) made =
further developments in probability theory. His work from 1550, titled <i>L=
iber de Ludo Aleae</i>, discussed the concepts of probability and how they =
were directly related to gambling. However, his work did not receive any im=
mediate recognition since it was not published until after his death. <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blaise_Pascal" title=3D"Blaise Pascal">=
Blaise Pascal</a> (1623=E2=80=931662) also contributed to probability theor=
y. His friend, Chevalier de M=C3=A9r=C3=A9, was an avid gambler with the go=
al to become wealthy from it.  De M=C3=A9r=C3=A9 tried a new mathematical a=
pproach to a gambling game but did not get the desired results. Determined =
to know why his strategy was unsuccessful, he consulted with Pascal. Pascal=
's work on this problem began an important correspondence between him and f=
ellow mathematician <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pierre_de_Ferm=
at" title=3D"Pierre de Fermat">Pierre de Fermat</a> (1601=E2=80=931665). Co=
mmunicating through letters, the two continued to exchange their ideas and =
thoughts. These interactions led to the conception of basic probability the=
ory. To this day, many gamblers still rely on the basic concepts of probabi=
lity theory in order to make informed decisions while gambling.<sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pok=
er_probability#cite_note-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-2" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poker_probability#cite_note-=
2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Frequencies">Frequencies</h=
2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DPoker_probabil=
ity&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: Frequencies">=
<span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span>=
</div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"5-card_poker_hands">5-card =
poker hands</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3D=
Poker_probability&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section:=
 5-card poker hands"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bra=
cket">]</span></span></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Video_poker_JoB_odds.svg" class=3D"mw-file-de=
scription"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb=
/8/80/Video_poker_JoB_odds.svg/250px-Video_poker_JoB_odds.svg.png" decoding=
=3D"async" width=3D"250" height=3D"318" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file=
-width=3D"792" data-file-height=3D"1008"></a><figcaption>An <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euler_diagram" title=3D"Euler diagram">Euler diag=
ram</a> depicting poker hands and their odds from a typical American 9/6 <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Video_poker#Jacks_or_Better" title=
=3D"Video poker">Jacks or Better</a> machine</figcaption></figure>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Straight_poker" class=3D"mw-=
redirect" title=3D"Straight poker">straight poker</a> and <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Five-card_draw" title=3D"Five-card draw">five-card =
draw</a>, where there are no <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hole_=
card" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Hole card">hole cards</a>, players are=
 simply dealt five cards from a deck of 52.
</p><p>The following chart <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enumera=
tion" title=3D"Enumeration">enumerates</a> the (absolute) <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frequency" title=3D"Frequency">frequency</a> of eac=
h hand, given all <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combination" tit=
le=3D"Combination">combinations</a> of five cards <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Random" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Random">randomly</a>=
 drawn from a full deck of 52 without replacement. <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Wild_Card_(card_games)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Wil=
d Card (card games)">Wild cards</a> are not considered. In this chart:
</p>
<ul><li><b>Distinct hands</b> are the number of different ways to draw the =
hand, not counting different suits.  In particular, a set of hands that all=
 tie each other is counted exactly once, not multiply.</li>
<li><b>Frequency</b> is the number of ways to draw the hand, <i>including</=
i> the same card values in different suits.</li>
<li>The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probability" title=3D"P=
robability">Probability</a></b> of drawing a given hand is calculated by di=
viding the number of ways of drawing the hand (<b>Frequency</b>) by the tot=
al number of 5-card hands (the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sam=
ple_space" title=3D"Sample space">sample space</a>; <span class=3D"mwe-math=
-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe=
-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.or=
g/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\textstyle {52 \choose 5}=3D2{,}598{,}960}"=
>
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mrow>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-OPEN">
              <mo maxsize=3D"1.2em" minsize=3D"1.2em">(</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mfrac linethickness=3D"0">
              <mn>52</mn>
              <mn>5</mn>
            </mfrac>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-CLOSE">
              <mo maxsize=3D"1.2em" minsize=3D"1.2em">)</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>2,598,960</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\textstyle {52 \choose 5}=
=3D2{,}598{,}960}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/99e48ad2d92fb1dc9cefe5c756c00552b32cbcca" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.171ex; width:16.303ex; height:3.509ex;" alt=3D"{\textstyle {52 \=
choose 5}=3D2{,}598{,}960}"></span>). For example, there are 4 different wa=
ys to draw a royal flush (one for each suit), so the probability is <span c=
lass=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">4</span><s=
pan class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">2,598,960</span></span>=
=E2=81=A0</span>, or one in 649,740. One would then expect to draw this han=
d about once in every 649,740 draws, or nearly 0.000154% of the time.</li>
<li><b>Cumulative probability</b> refers to the probability of drawing a ha=
nd as good as <i>or better than</i> the specified one. For example, the pro=
bability of drawing three of a kind is approximately 2.11%, while the proba=
bility of drawing a hand <i>at least</i> as good as three of a kind is abou=
t 2.87%. The cumulative probability is determined by adding one hand's prob=
ability with the probabilities of all hands above it.</li>
<li>The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Odds" title=3D"Odds">Od=
ds</a></b> are defined as the ratio of the number of ways <i>not</i> to dra=
w the hand, to the number of ways to draw it. In statistics, this is called=
 <b>odds against</b>. For instance, with a royal flush, there are 4 ways to=
 draw one, and 2,598,956 ways to draw something else, so the odds against d=
rawing a royal flush are 2,598,956&nbsp;: 4, or 649,739&nbsp;: 1. The formu=
la for establishing the odds can also be stated as <i>(1/p) =E2=80=93 1&nbs=
p;: 1</i>, where <i>p</i> is the aforementioned probability.</li>
<li>The values given for <b>Probability</b>, <b>Cumulative probability</b>,=
 and <b>Odds</b> are rounded off for simplicity; the <b>Distinct hands</b> =
and <b>Frequency</b> values are exact.</li></ul>
<p>The <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binomial_coefficient" ti=
tle=3D"Binomial coefficient">nCr</a></i> or <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Binomial_coefficient" title=3D"Binomial coefficient">nCk</a></=
i> function on most scientific calculators can be used to calculate hand fr=
equencies; entering <code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-text mw-c=
ontent-ltr" style=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">nCr</code> with <code class=3D"mw-highli=
ght mw-highlight-lang-text mw-content-ltr" style=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">52</code>=
 and <code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-text mw-content-ltr" sty=
