ass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">See also: <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lowball_(poker)" title=3D"Lowball (p=
oker)">Lowball (poker)</a></div>
<p>Some variants of poker, called <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Lowball_(poker)" title=3D"Lowball (poker)">lowball</a>, use a <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Low_hand" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Low ha=
nd">low hand</a> to determine the winning hand.  In most variants of lowbal=
l, the ace is counted as the lowest card and straights and flushes don't co=
unt against a low hand, so the lowest hand is the five-high hand <b>A-2-3-4=
-5</b>, also called a <i>wheel</i>.  The probability is calculated based on=
