</p><p>If aces are not low, simply rotate the hand descriptions so that 6-h=
igh replaces 5-high for the best hand and ace-high replaces king-high as th=
e worst hand.
</p><p>Some players do not ignore straights and flushes when computing the =
low hand in lowball. In this case, the lowest hand is <b>A-2-3-4-6</b> with=
 at least two suits. Probabilities are adjusted in the above table such tha=
t "5-high" is not listed, "6-high" has 781,824 distinct hands, and "King-hi=
gh" has 21,457,920 distinct hands, respectively. The Total line also needs =
adjusting.
</p>
